Introduction

Organizations receive hundreds of customer support requests every day through emails, websites, and customer portals. Manually reading, categorizing, and assigning these tickets to the correct support team is time-consuming and often results in delays. TicketSense is a Flask-based web application that automates ticket classification and routing using predefined categories and intelligent logic. The application provides a simple interface where users can submit support requests, and the system automatically categorizes and routes them to the appropriate department.

Part 1 – Project Case Study
1. Problem Statement

Organizations face challenges in managing customer support tickets efficiently. Most helpdesk systems require manual categorization and assignment, causing:

Delayed response times
Human errors in ticket classification
Increased workload for support staff
Poor customer satisfaction
Difficulty in tracking ticket status

The objective of TicketSense is to automate ticket categorization and routing, thereby improving efficiency and reducing response time.

2. Existing System Analysis

Traditional helpdesk systems generally work as follows:

Customers submit tickets manually.
Support executives read each ticket.
Tickets are manually categorized.
Tickets are assigned to different departments.
Staff members update ticket status manually.

Examples include:

Email-based customer support
Spreadsheet-based ticket tracking
Manual CRM ticket systems

Although commercial helpdesk platforms provide automation, they are often expensive and complex for small organizations.

3. Drawbacks of Existing System

The current systems have several limitations:

Manual ticket classification
Slow response time
Human mistakes
Duplicate ticket handling
High operational cost
Difficult to scale
Poor workload distribution
Limited reporting capabilities
4. Proposed Solution

TicketSense provides an automated helpdesk ticket management system developed using Flask.

The system:

Accepts customer support requests
Automatically identifies ticket category
Routes tickets to the correct department
Displays ticket information
Maintains ticket records
Provides faster processing

This reduces manual work while improving ticket management efficiency.

5. Objectives of the Project

The primary objectives are:

Automate ticket classification
Improve customer response time
Reduce manual intervention
Provide an easy-to-use web interface
Improve routing accuracy
Maintain organized ticket records
Enhance productivity of support teams
